<TITLE> Women's college in every upazila, vows Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Mushtak Amed bdnews24.com correspondent Gopalganj, Dec 17 (bdnews24.com)  Awami League president Sheikh Hasina, addressing local leaders in her home town of Tungipara, Wednesday afternoon, promised women's colleges in every upazila if her party came to power. Hasina will be electioneering in her hometown through the day, as she is running from the constituency, Gopalganj-3. The former prime minister is scheduled to continue from there on a three-day election tour of southwestern districts, accompanied by her sister Sheikh Rehana and niece Ajmina Siddiqui Ruponti. She left the capital on Tuesday and addressed a number of public gatherings in Munshiganj, Faridpur and Madaripur. According to AL leaders, the party chief would stay the whole day in Gopalganj and address a public rally at Kotalipara College. On Thursday, the last day of her trip, Hasina is scheduled to speak in public meetings in Bagerhat, Jessore and Khulna. The chief of AL-led grand alliance hit the campaign trail by addressing public rallies in Dhaka on Monday. Hasina is running election from two other constituencies, Rangpur and Bagerhat. b
